values:
&nbsp;im not too sure about what to do anymore. eh...but what else is new? just when i thot my life was looking up and my happy meter was rising; it all comes to a crashing halt. i've been analoging it to a ship which has sailed, been&nbsp;devoured by the Kraken, then ran into an iceburg. it's slowly sinking as we speak. and the longer i stall, the worse it gets.&nbsp;

to me at least...i feel kinda helpless in the situation. i want to accept that the ship's going down and move on, but my friend is trying to deter me from that conclusion. and a part of me doesn't really want to give up. that part wants to try again to see if we can fix the mess im in. however, that's like 5% of me against the other 90. the other 5% just doesn't give a shit. (lol)

its an emotional situation which is buggin the crap outta me b/c i don't really know what i want to do about things. (ie it concerns a guy duh! lol) emotions are tricky things. they are never black&amp;white, always shades of grey. therein i am all over the place with these things.&nbsp;basically, when i first met him i was really happy, confused, but happy. like i didn't know if i liked him like THAT&nbsp;yet&nbsp;;o) so i&nbsp;was just gonna play it by ear. i was logical in the&nbsp;whole thing. "he's not even that cute, don't get too bent out of shape about it. your just making a new friend. new friends are exciting"&nbsp;

NEVERTHELESS, i did a capital job of screwing things up between us by being my awesome, nerdy, studious self. i get so absorbed and panicked in&nbsp;my endeavors to not fail that&nbsp;i lost touch with reality. i wish i could explain that to him....but i can't not anymore. cause im pretty sure he&nbsp;hates me. i've had soooo many opportunitys to change this but i've&nbsp;let them all pass by me. i realise that the moment existED, and make up an excuse as to why i let it pass. i'm pretty pathetic, i know...

i just want him to talk to me again i guess. im a sucker 4 a high--an emotional high. &nbsp;im starting to realize i get addicted to the happy feelings someone gives me and not necessarily the person. they matter at the time, but afterwards...i crave the emotions i experienced. it's putry messed up haha but that's a new revelation so it's still in the workings.

i know what i need to do to fix my situation. i need to talk to him. strike up conversation somehow. im good at planning those things out in my head so hopefully things go okay.&nbsp;

i don't need him to like me, i just want things between us to be cool....&nbsp;
yeah, that's it....

so its christmastime, and&nbsp;i took my last set of finals&nbsp;this morning.

i'm stoked to say the least.&nbsp;

However, there's a cloud&nbsp;looming over my head,&nbsp;preparing to cause a downpour.
That cloud being a certain person i've had my eye on lately...kinda.
idon'tknow...its complicated
*chuckles*&nbsp;
yeah what else is new?

i just wish...i knew how i felt about him.&nbsp;like really.&nbsp;im still in the Confusion stage, where you think you like somebody but you're not quite sure yet. im beginning to think that we might be friends at least. and i think that might be really cool too. *shrugs* i'm making things way too serious in my head. that's my problem...that's prolly why im in the pickle im in.&nbsp;

It has dawned on me, thanks to my friend, that he thinks i'm ignoring him...maybe. either way, its not good. i'm not ignoring him. or not trying to...argh! i can't help that i focus grossingly on my studies and block out everything else. i can't help that i'm not an outgoing person who talks to people in the morning like he does. im just not social....especially when im freaking out about school.&nbsp;

i wanted to make things right today, but...they was a no-go. i kept missing my opportunities. *sigh* i'm such a loser. i kill things before they even have a chance to live. we've talked all of...2, serious, one-on-one times. and those were nice...like really cool. the kind of convos i wouldn't&nbsp;mind having more of once and awhile. the pointless, thought-provoking, occasionally deep conversations that we all know and love. haha.

...argh! i hate being this way...obsessing that is. i need to...forget. about him, about emotions, about the people who take up my life...that's y im looking forward to this break so much. whether they believe it or not, my family keeps me sane. *smirks* i retreat into them @ just the right times so i can forget about everything. that is...until grades are calculated and posted. *bleh*

but whatever. i&nbsp;need to go plan...and knit. can i help that Degrassi is so addicting?&nbsp;

:D&nbsp;

oh alonzo, sometimes i wish you were real. (haha) yesterday was full of highs and lows. i'd like to forget about the angry jealous part (the movies) and the hyper unnecessary part (the coffee) and forcus on what happened after all that.&nbsp;

that night, i looked up at the stars for the first time in...years. and it was AMAZING! but not just amazing, like better than amazing. exhilarating? or some other fancy word that means something better than that even. *sigh* it was just wonderful. and it was then that i realized what i&nbsp;wanted in life...somewhat. i couldn't do a full on amazed wonder like i would have liked to b/c i was in a car&nbsp;at the time and there were streetlights getting in the way. but if i was able to ponder the full&nbsp;glory of the time, then i would have been able to sort out all the things that were going on in my life.&nbsp;alas, i could only lick the surface.&nbsp;

and that surface includes&nbsp;an aspect of&nbsp;what&nbsp;my ideal person would be.&nbsp;here's what i was able to come up with: we would lay on the beach&nbsp;and have an intellectual and philosophical discussion about life and everything. nerdy, i know. (haha) but we'd also listen to music that we are both into, sing along, maybe they'd play me a song on thier acoustic guitar and it would be momentary bliss. then the clicheness of the mood would set in and i think you can guess what will happen next. let your imaginations roam asunder. (haha)

and all this by looking up at the night sky. i am awesome

and that is when everything decided to go downhill. and i find myself helping my ex hook up with another girl. not so awesome. i wish i was so paranoid about this, cause when he told me then asked for my help, it felt way too weird and...scripted? like it was so storybook it was crazy. at least the things he said were. thanks for ruining my good mood...so now i need to figure out a way to ask someone who im not too incredibly close with what they think of him. this is not my thing. i wish i wasn't the person doing it. if it was happening, ok w/e but now that im apart of the thing, i hate it.&nbsp;

he's the 2nd one to fall for her. im just waiting til the day i realize that i'm the one who is also madly in love with her.&nbsp;
fucking ridiculous...

&nbsp;so guess what alonzo?
Cheese is "back and better than ever!" haha
our convo last night to the early morning was quite enjoyable...
i just wish i wasn't an anxious tardface who is paranoid of his motives.
but maybe i have a right to be?

he never did anything "bad" to make me skeptical of him or anything,
its just dude, i don't want to have sex with you. period.&nbsp;
haha
i mean how many times do i have to say it to get it thru to you?
and i hate how vulnerable i make myself&nbsp;
so that people like him can prey upon me and use me/ my emotions to their advantage
but when i try to do the same, i feel horrible.
guess that's the diff b/w u and me kiddo...

people have THE best timing when it comes to walking into my life
the plot always twists when i least expect it.&nbsp;
"but i thot you were dead Johnny? i saw you fall off that cliff 5 months ago! how can this be?" "well im back baby! and im ready for action!"
i secretly love it, don'tcha know.&nbsp;
it helps me keep my mind off of some things. helps me to redivert my attention.
this could be good or bad depending on the situations at hand.&nbsp;

like at the time of our convo, i was writing a history essay.&nbsp;
i took a 2 hour assignment and stretched it out to about 5 or so.&nbsp;
its ridiculous i know...
